[SN]TITLE[SN]
Birmingham homes heated by residents' sewage gas

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
For the first time in the UK, Severn Trent Water is supplying gas generated by one of the region's sewage plants into the National Grid.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
2 October 2014 Last updated at 09:05 BST
The plant in Minworth, Warwickshire, treats the waste of two-and-a-half million people in Birmingham, and the gas will provide enough energy to help power about 4,000 homes.
BBC Midlands Today's science correspondent, David Gregory-Kumar, has been finding out more.
